there is another handyman.

295
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:19,110
But he's new here.

296
00:14:19,590 --> 00:14:22,230
So we only put him to serve tea

297
00:14:22,230 --> 00:14:23,230
and do odd jobs.

298
00:14:27,220 --> 00:14:29,400
The sewage in the kitchen leads to the Underground Culvert.

299
00:14:30,150 --> 00:14:31,150
The cover

300
00:14:31,150 --> 00:14:32,880
seems to have been moved recently.

301
00:14:34,150 --> 00:14:34,790
Manager.

302
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:37,230
Can you get the handyman

303
00:14:37,230 --> 00:14:38,200
you just mentioned?

304
00:14:39,150 --> 00:14:40,000
I'll get him.

305
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,000
Officer.

306
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:55,030
Did you see anyone suspicious

307
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:57,440
when the incident occurred today?

308
00:14:59,670 --> 00:15:00,400
Not really.

309
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:02,550
Where were you at the time?

310
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:04,280
We were busy today

311
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:06,080
and I was sent to help in the kitchen.

312
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:07,760
That's true.

313
00:15:09,650 --> 00:15:10,700
What's with your hand?

314
00:15:11,370 --> 00:15:12,130
It's nothing.

315
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,490
I got bitten by a mad dog.

316
00:15:21,820 --> 00:15:23,910
Where were you last night?

317
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:27,760
I was on duty at the restaurant.

318
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:30,110
I was right here.

319
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,350
Did you see anything unusual?

320
00:15:35,110 --> 00:15:35,760
No.

321
00:15:36,520 --> 00:15:36,960
All right.

322
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:39,110
Thank you for your time.

323
00:15:40,150 --> 00:15:40,880
You may leave.

324
00:15:46,910 --> 00:15:47,470
Have you

325
00:15:47,470 --> 00:15:48,520
found any clues?

326
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,960
We'll see tonight.

327
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:53,150
All right.

328
00:16:00,620 --> 00:16:02,140
Have some wonton.

329
00:16:02,850 --> 00:16:04,080
Fresh out of the pot.

330
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:05,400
I'm stuffed.

331
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:07,760
We can go.

332
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:09,910
Already?

333
00:16:10,290 --> 00:16:11,580
Have some wonton.

334
00:16:12,550 --> 00:16:13,760
What else do you want?

335
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:17,020
[Office of Justice]

336
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:20,880
You want to see Zhao Mo?

337
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:22,400
Then just say it.

338
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,030
I ended up having so many wontons

339
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,910
outside the Office of Justice.

340
00:16:27,350 --> 00:16:28,150
Father.

341
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:30,350
Let's check on my brother.

342
00:16:30,350 --> 00:16:31,710
Why would I?

343
00:16:32,350 --> 00:16:33,790
He doesn't see me as his father.

344
00:16:33,790 --> 00:16:35,670
And I should beg him to be my son?

345
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:37,910
He was like,

346
00:16:38,590 --> 00:16:39,740
"Am I your biological son?"

347
00:16:39,740 --> 00:16:40,910
Of course, he is.

348
00:16:42,580 --> 00:16:43,880
Who else can be his father?

349
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:47,800
Father, that's not what Mo meant.

350
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:48,540
What did he mean?

351
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:50,600
He didn't say you weren't his father.

352
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:52,560
Go ahead

353
00:16:53,550 --> 00:16:54,550
if you want to see him.

354
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,200
I'm stuffed. See you at home.

355
00:16:58,640 --> 00:16:59,440
I'm off.

356
00:16:59,520 --> 00:17:00,320
Father.

357
00:17:00,670 --> 00:17:02,280
Father, don't get lost.

358
00:17:02,470 --> 00:17:03,110
Rest assured.

359
00:17:07,930 --> 00:17:09,690
Have some wonton.

360
00:17:20,820 --> 00:17:24,020
[Office of Justice]

361
00:17:26,830 --> 00:17:27,920
Mo, you're heading out?

362
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:38,180
Have some wonton.

363
00:17:38,780 --> 00:17:40,010
Fresh out of the pot.

364
00:17:42,090 --> 00:17:43,050
Wonton.

365
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,070
Why did you come?

366
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:51,280
I won't go home.

367
00:17:51,470 --> 00:17:52,830
Don't flatter yourself.

368
00:17:53,490 --> 00:17:54,780
I'm not asking you to come home.

369
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:05,830
What's wrong?

370
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:07,230
Nothing.

371
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:11,680
I know

372
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:14,280
you're still mad about what happened in the morning.

373
00:18:16,050 --> 00:18:18,200
It's easy to repay someone who gave birth to me

374
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:19,570
but didn't raise me,

375
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,560
while it's hard to repay someone

376
00:18:22,350 --> 00:18:23,440
who did the opposite.

377
00:18:24,510 --> 00:18:26,030
I totally understand.

378
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:29,110
Even if we're not bound by blood,

379
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:31,390
it doesn't change the fact

380
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:34,560
that Father and Buyou are my family.

381
00:18:35,150 --> 00:18:36,630
But I have to figure out

382
00:18:36,630 --> 00:18:37,960
who I really am.

383
00:18:38,110 --> 00:18:39,680
This is the meaning

384
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:40,990
of my life.

385
00:18:42,390 --> 00:18:44,800
I must figure out what's going on

386
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:47,030
to learn to face it.

387
00:18:47,230 --> 00:18:48,350
But

388
00:18:48,990 --> 00:18:50,510
you're not guaranteed

389
00:18:50,930 --> 00:18:51,750
to find a closure

390
00:18:51,750 --> 00:18:53,110
even if you face it.

391
00:18:57,030 --> 00:18:58,270
Wouldn't you want to know

392
00:18:58,440 --> 00:18:59,800
who you are?

393
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,560
I just want to be with my family.

394
00:19:16,630 --> 00:19:17,680
Are you coming home tonight?

395
00:19:19,990 --> 00:19:21,750
I fought with Buyou so badly this morning.

396
00:19:22,750 --> 00:19:23,840
So maybe not.

397
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:28,560
In that case,

398
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:30,750
forget about the wonton.

399
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:31,600
You can leave.

400
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:38,800
Pay the bill.

401
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:39,920
Four bowls in total.

402
00:20:17,030 --> 00:20:18,680
Come on, the wonton is ready.

403
00:20:20,270 --> 00:20:21,200
Look.

404
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:23,840
The Office of Justice is right there.

405
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:25,960
[Office of Justice]
Let's report to the authorities.

406
00:20:26,110 --> 00:20:26,560
Su.

407
00:20:27,230 --> 00:20:28,750
Your mother might be back soon.

408
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:30,230
Let's wait a bit more, okay?

409
00:20:30,230 --> 00:20:31,960
But I miss my mother.

410
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:33,270
Let's report it now.

411
00:20:33,270 --> 00:20:34,110
Mr. He?

412
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:36,720
Ban.

413
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:41,080
Aren't you

414
00:20:41,270 --> 00:20:42,990
the little fighter?

415
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:44,080
What happened?

416
00:20:44,870 --> 00:20:46,720
Su's mother left the city to purchase goods

417
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:48,030
and entrusted her to us.

418
00:20:48,110 --> 00:20:49,350
She must have been delayed.

419
00:20:49,350 --> 00:20:50,630
But it's been five days.

420
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:51,780
My mother said

421
00:20:51,780 --> 00:20:53,750
that she'd be back in three days.

422
00:20:55,750 --> 00:20:57,510
So your name is Su.

423
00:20:57,840 --> 00:20:59,870
I saw how brave you were at the Welfare Center.

424
00:21:00,350 --> 00:21:02,230
I was just like that when I was a kid.

425
00:21:02,840 --> 00:21:04,350
I never cry.

426
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:10,150
But I miss my mother a bit.

427
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:12,630
My mother is missing.

428
00:21:12,840 --> 00:21:14,870
Auntie Song is also missing.

429
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:17,200
And Auntie Lu rarely comes back.

430
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:20,150
Don't they want me anymore?

431
00:21:20,270 --> 00:21:22,030
Am I going to be homeless?

432
00:21:22,390 --> 00:21:23,630
No way.

433
00:21:23,630 --> 00:21:24,800
You won't be homeless.

434
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:26,030
No way.

435
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:29,230
Is there anyone else in your family?

436
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:30,840
No.

437
00:21:31,630 --> 00:21:33,480
Su lives in the embroidery workshop

438
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:35,390
with her mother Ci

439
00:21:35,390 --> 00:21:36,230
and her two aunts.

440
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,230
Su calls them Aunties.

441
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:40,440
She has no one else.

442
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,080
Look.

443
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:45,680
You are so well dressed

444
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:47,350
and your hair is so neatly combed.

445
00:21:47,870 --> 00:21:50,510
Your mother and aunties must love you very much.

446
00:21:50,510 --> 00:21:51,800
I wasn't so lucky as a kid.

447
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:54,440
I had to wear my second brother's old clothes.

448
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:56,350
The two hair buns

449
00:21:56,350 --> 00:21:57,480
my eldest brother tied

450
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:59,320
were always uneven.

451
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:02,390
The kids in the alley used to laugh at me

452
00:22:02,390 --> 00:22:03,920
about my "crooked corners".

453
00:22:05,030 --> 00:22:05,600
Let's go.

454
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:07,440
Let me walk you home, okay?

455
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:08,000
Okay.

456
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,560
Maybe your mother is waiting for you.

457
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:10,390
Really?

458
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:12,080
- Let's go. Let's hold hands. - Let's go.

459
00:22:12,510 --> 00:22:13,560
Want to hold hands?

460
00:22:14,230 --> 00:22:15,350
Let's go.

461
00:22:16,230 --> 00:22:16,800
Let's go.

462
00:22:18,750 --> 00:22:19,630
Here.

463
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:21,210
Su.

464
00:22:21,560 --> 00:22:23,510
- Excuse me. - My father

465
00:22:23,510 --> 00:22:26,270
got lost once before.

466
00:22:26,630 --> 00:22:27,560
I cried every day

467
00:22:27,560 --> 00:22:29,150
while searching for him.

468
00:22:29,560 --> 00:22:30,750
But then one day,

469
00:22:30,750 --> 00:22:31,680
somehow...

470
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:33,800
- Excuse me. - He came back on his own.

471
00:22:34,570 --> 00:22:35,480
Sister.

472
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:37,720
This is our embroidery workshop.

473
00:22:38,390 --> 00:22:40,110
Jinxiu Embroidery.

474
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:43,030
It closes so early?

475
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:46,840
Ever since my mother left,

476
00:22:46,990 --> 00:22:49,600
we've been closing early.

477
00:22:51,920 --> 00:22:52,750
Su.

478
00:22:52,990 --> 00:22:54,230
Now that you are home,

479
00:22:54,230 --> 00:22:55,270
I have to go.

480
00:22:55,270 --> 00:22:55,920
- Come on. - Okay.

481
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:56,720
- Excuse me. - Don't worry.

482
00:22:56,720 --> 00:22:57,990
- Your mother will surely come back. - Groceries.

483
00:22:58,170 --> 00:23:00,080
Pendants. Take a look.

484
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:01,160
I have work to do.

485
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:02,230
Okay.

486
00:23:02,230 --> 00:23:03,630
Thank you, He Huan.

487
00:23:04,870 --> 00:23:05,800
Ban.

488
00:23:06,270 --> 00:23:07,720
Let me show you my house.

489
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:08,480
Okay.

490
00:23:08,480 --> 00:23:09,110
Let's go.

491
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:10,230
From there.

492
00:23:10,230 --> 00:23:10,870
Back door.

493
00:23:10,870 --> 00:23:12,230
- You have a back door? - Miss.

494
00:23:12,230 --> 00:23:13,210
Come and take a look.

495
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:16,270
Our home is right inside.

496
00:23:16,630 --> 00:23:17,750
Here. Yeah.

497
00:23:17,990 --> 00:23:18,560
Right here.

498
00:23:22,390 --> 00:23:25,200
I live here with my mother.

499
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:28,390
Auntie Song and Auntie Lu live there.

500
00:23:30,750 --> 00:23:33,150
So you have three embroiderers.

501
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:36,990
Auntie Lu stayed to look after the workshop and didn't teach embroidery

502
00:23:37,230 --> 00:23:39,150
at the welfare house last time.

503
00:23:39,150 --> 00:23:39,870
I see.

504
00:23:40,150 --> 00:23:42,150
My mother and I live in that room.

505
00:23:42,150 --> 00:23:43,350
Let me show you.

506
00:23:43,390 --> 00:23:44,030
Is that fine?

507
00:23:44,030 --> 00:23:44,960
Of course.

508
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:45,800
Let's go.

509
00:23:45,990 --> 00:23:46,480
Let's go.

510
00:23:51,030 --> 00:23:52,750
Come on in.

511
00:23:53,230 --> 00:23:55,480
This is the room for you and your mother?

512
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:56,480
That's right.

513
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:57,870
Look. She embroidered this.

514
00:23:57,870 --> 00:23:59,110
It's pretty, right?

515
00:23:59,230 --> 00:24:00,680
Your mother made all these?

516
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:01,480
That's right.

517
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:03,750
So pretty.

518
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:05,720
Excellent embroidery work.

519
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:10,110
This one

520
00:24:10,270 --> 00:24:12,600
seems a bit worse

521
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:14,200
than the other embroidery.

522
00:24:15,270 --> 00:24:16,920
I bet this is not your mother's work.

523
00:24:19,840 --> 00:24:21,560
Ci Rou?

524
00:24:22,080 --> 00:24:22,870
No.

525
00:24:23,320 --> 00:24:25,990
My mother said she found it on the street.

526
00:24:26,630 --> 00:24:27,750
- She did? - Who are you?

527
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:29,480
Why are you in our house?

528
00:24:31,210 --> 00:24:32,440
[Lu Sanzhen, Embroiderer]
I-I'm here...

529
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:33,580
Auntie Lu.

530
00:24:34,990 --> 00:24:36,720
This is Sister Zhao Ban.

531
00:24:37,270 --> 00:24:40,720
I asked her to help me find my mother.

532
00:24:42,390 --> 00:24:43,200
Nonsense.

533
00:24:44,030 --> 00:24:44,600
Su.

534
00:24:45,230 --> 00:24:46,920
Didn't I tell you that your mother

535
00:24:46,990 --> 00:24:47,960
went to buy goods?

536
00:24:51,110 --> 00:24:52,150
Just a second, please.

537
00:24:52,150 --> 00:24:53,270
I have something to do.

538
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:54,440
No rush.

539
00:24:54,440 --> 00:24:55,440
Take your time, Lady Lu.

540
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:56,800
I'll check out the house first.

541
00:25:00,150 --> 00:25:00,630
But...

542
00:25:00,720 --> 00:25:02,870
But my mother has been gone for days.

543
00:25:02,870 --> 00:25:04,870
I miss her.

544
00:25:06,350 --> 00:25:08,080
But you can't just

545
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:09,350
take a stranger home.

546
00:25:10,510 --> 00:25:11,080
Okay.

547
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:14,920
Sister, let me walk you out.

548
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:23,720
Sister.

549
00:25:23,720 --> 00:25:24,990
Sorry.

550
00:25:24,990 --> 00:25:26,560
Don't be mad at Auntie Lu.

551
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:27,800
It's okay.

552
00:25:28,510 --> 00:25:30,630
Is she close to your mother?

553
00:25:30,630 --> 00:25:31,390
Yes.

554
00:25:31,990 --> 00:25:34,080
They've always been close.

555
00:25:36,030 --> 00:25:37,630
Why isn't your Auntie Song here?

556
00:25:38,230 --> 00:25:42,270
My mother said that Auntie Song went back to her hometown.

557
00:25:43,990 --> 00:25:44,560
Su.

558
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:47,920
Do you know where your mother went to purchase goods?

559
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:51,480
A few days ago, Auntie Lu said she went to Xiangfu.

560
00:25:51,510 --> 00:25:53,230
Xiangfu? That's not far.

561
00:25:53,480 --> 00:25:54,110
Listen.

562
00:25:54,320 --> 00:25:56,840
I'll ask my friend to look for your mother there.

563
00:25:56,840 --> 00:25:58,480
I'll keep you updated, okay?

564
00:25:58,480 --> 00:25:59,270
Okay.

565
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:01,680
Go back. I'm going home too.

566
00:26:02,870 --> 00:26:04,150
Sister.

567
00:26:04,150 --> 00:26:05,510
Where do you live?

568
00:26:05,510 --> 00:26:06,320
Me?

569
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:07,720
I live in Sparrow Lane.

570
00:26:07,720 --> 00:26:08,320
Over there.

571
00:26:09,080 --> 00:26:10,150
There is a persimmon tree

572
00:26:10,150 --> 00:26:11,480
in our yard.

573
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:12,480
That's my home.

574
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:14,720
Go back.

575
00:26:14,800 --> 00:26:15,560
See you.

576
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:16,200
See you.

577
00:26:33,630 --> 00:26:34,840
I'll leave you to handle

578
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:36,110
the embroidery workshop.

579
00:26:37,960 --> 00:26:39,230
Rest assured. Leave it to me.

580
00:26:39,630 --> 00:26:40,270
Please stay.

581
00:26:52,990 --> 00:26:54,110
Excuse me.

582
00:26:56,870 --> 00:26:58,230
Now I remember.

583
00:26:58,680 --> 00:27:00,110
Your family wanted to buy a house.

584
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:02,110
No wonder you looked familiar.

585
00:27:02,630 --> 00:27:03,600
Well...

586
00:27:03,990 --> 00:27:04,750
Excuse me.

587
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,690
